      • addAnalytic

        public void addAnalytic(Map<String,Object> params,
               ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Record an analytic record for a known state within the application.

        Target API Endpoint: /analytics/usage

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.tag of type String
          The tag to apply: the name of the action or thing being logged.
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The logged in user ID
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          The application key unique to each application.
        • SirqulKeys.appVersion of type AppVersion
          The current build version of the application
        • SirqulKeys.device of type String
          The name of the device being used (iPhone5,1 , HTC Nexus One, x86_64, etc.)
        • SirqulKeys.deviceType of type String
          The type of device (Handheld or Desktop)
        • SirqulKeys.deviceOS of type String
          The operating system that the device is using (iPhone OS 5.0, Android OS 2.3.6, Windows 7 Service Pack 1, etc.)
        • SirqulKeys.model of type String
          The model of the device (iPhone5,1 , Nexus One, etc.)
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the location
        • SirqulKeys.customId of type Long
          A customId used to associate the usage record with some other record in the system
        • SirqulKeys.achievementIncrement of type Long
          Determines how many achievement points and/or ranking points the user gets if this analytic is associated with an achievement
        • SirqulKeys.city of type String
          The current city of the user
        • SirqulKeys.state of type String
          The current state of the user
        • SirqulKeys.country of type String
          The current country of the user
        • SirqulKeys.zip of type String
          The current zip of the user
        • SirqulKeys.locationDescription of type String
          The general description of the user's location
        • SirqulKeys.clientTime of type Long
          Timestamp sent from device

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        AnalyticsObject.addAnalytic(...)

      • createGriplyUrlWithAnalytics

        public String createGriplyUrlWithAnalytics(String griplyUrl,
                                  String appKey,
                                  Map<String,String> parameters)
                                    throws UnsupportedEncodingException
        Locally construct a griply url with analytics appended. This is a thread safe method and makes no network calls.
        Parameters:
        griplyUrl - the griply url to have values appended to
        appKey - the application key
        parameters - the parameters, where the keys are the parameters of the /analytics/usage api, and values are the values you'd like for each parameter.
        Returns:
        the string
        Throws:
        UnsupportedEncodingException - if a values cannot be encoded via URLEncoder with "UTF-8" charset.
        See Also:
        AnalyticsApiBase.createGriplyUrlWithAnalytics(...)

      • getAnalyticsAggregatedFiltered

        public void getAnalyticsAggregatedFiltered(Map<String,Object> params,
                                  ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Query analytics to get data used for nested graphs and charts.

        Target API Endpoint: /analytics/aggregatedFilteredUsage

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          The application key used to filter results by application
        • SirqulKeys.startDate of type Long
          Used to search for results after or equal to this date (UNIX time-stamp in milliseconds)
        • SirqulKeys.endDate of type Long
          Used to search for results before or equal to this date (UNIX time-stamp in milliseconds)
        • SirqulKeys.device of type String
          The device to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        • SirqulKeys.deviceType of type String
          The device type to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        • SirqulKeys.deviceOS of type String
          The device OS to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        • SirqulKeys.model of type String
          The model to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.gender of type Enums.AudienceGender
          The gender to filter results by {MALE, FEMALE}
        • SirqulKeys.ageGroup of type Enums.AgeGroup
          Comma separated list of age groups to filter by {AGE_0_13, AGE_14_17, AGE_18_22, AGE_23_30, AGE_31_54, AGE_55_PLUS}
        • SirqulKeys.country of type String
          The country to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.state of type String
          The state to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.city of type String
          The city to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.zip of type String
          The zip to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.tag of type String
          The tag to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.userAccountId of type Long
          The account id to filter results for a particular user
        • SirqulKeys.userAccountDisplay of type String
          The user display to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.userAccountUsername of type String
          The username to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        • SirqulKeys.groupByRoot of type Enums.AnalyticsApiMap
          Determines how to group results. For example, passing in 'CREATED' will return results by date. Passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return results by user {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, APPLICATION_NAME_BY_ID}
        • SirqulKeys.groupBy of type Enums.AnalyticsApiMap
          Determines how to group the nested data. {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, APPLICATION_NAME_BY_ID}
        • SirqulKeys.distinctCount of type Enums.AnalyticsApiMap
          Performs a unique query on the specified column. For example, passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return the number of unique users. {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, NEW_ACCOUNT}
        • SirqulKeys.sortField of type Enums.AnalyticsApiMap
          Determines whether the results will be sorted by day or by number of hits {CREATED, TAG_COUNT}
        • SirqulKeys.descending of type Boolean
          Determines whether to return results in descending order
        • SirqulKeys.hideUnknown of type Boolean
          Determines whether to return data that has empty or unknown values
        • SirqulKeys.responseFormat of type Enums.ResponseFormat
          Determines whether to return a JOSN or XML representation of the graph results
        • SirqulKeys.limit of type Integer
          Used to limit results to get a cleaner graph. The results that gets filtered out will be combined
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the current location of the user

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        String if responseFormat equals Enums.ResponseFormat.XML and ChartData if responseFormat equals any other Enums.ResponseFormat. On error, returns SirqulResponse with message.
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<@link String}, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        AnalyticsApiBase.getAnalyticsAggregatedFiltered(...)
